The ^*BCanadian National Team Championships^*N tooks place last week in Montreal. Congratulations to ^*BNick Gartaganis-Judy Gartaganis^*N and ^*BKeith Balcombe-Gord Campbell^*N who beat ^*BPaul Thurston-Rick Delogu^*N, ^*BMichael Roche-Gloria Silverman^*N, and ^*BAndy Altay-Ian McKinnon^*N 152-143 over a well-played and hard-fought 72-board match.

This entire match was broadcast  as ^*BFree Live Online Vugraph^*N through ^*BBridge Base Online^*N. In total more than 1000 people watched parts of this broadcast and there was often more than 100 people watching at any given time. ^*BBridge Base Inc.^*N President ^*BFred Gitelman^*N and other Canadian experts provided commentary and analysis as the match was being played. We would like to thank the ^*BCanadian Bridge Federation^*N and ^*BJude Goodwin^*N for their support 

Despite a few glitches in the software and a flaky Internet connection at the playing site, this broadcast was a huge success and we received a great deal of positive feedback. We are very confident that this medium has a great deal to offer to all bridge players and we are committed to keeping these broadcasts free.

