This years CNTC final was special for a number of reasons. It was the first bridge tournament played in Canada ever to be broadcast live on the Internet (and one of the first anywhere). It was also a great match. The Gartaganis team led throughout until Thurston took a 3-IMP lead on the third last board. The last 2 boards looked flat and it appeared that Thurston would win until Keith Balcombe and Gord Campbell produced a great effort on the second last board to snatch victory from the jaws of defeat for the Gartaganis team. It made for a thrilling and dramatic vugraph broadcast. Thanks to all the players who really gave it their all in this match!

This was the first time in the history of the CNTC that the final two teams both contained a woman player. Judy Gartaganis and Gloria Silverman proved beyond any doubt that women can compete at this level. These two want to be the best bridge players in their country, not just the best bridge players of their gender. Our hats go off to them!

Both Judy and Gloria were involved in this week's deal. This deal took play during the 3rd quarter of the finals of the 2001 CNTC. The deal has been rotated to make south the declarer.|
